a parenting style

00:50:00.430 --> 00:50:03.430
back who knows how
many generations that

00:50:03.430 --> 00:50:07.070
was like Taylor and
Tiffany's, and that

00:50:07.070 --> 00:50:10.570
was appropriate for
the time and the place.

00:50:10.570 --> 00:50:14.410
And it might not have
worked in 16th century

00:50:14.410 --> 00:50:19.280
Bologna or something,
or with a kid who was

00:50:19.280 --> 00:50:21.050
interested in something else.

00:50:21.050 --> 00:50:23.300
But a lot of things
lined up for Taylor,

00:50:23.300 --> 00:50:28.610
just a lot of what makes
these gifted kids succeed

00:50:28.610 --> 00:50:31.140
is actually luck.

00:50:31.140 --> 00:50:31.890
They need support.

00:50:31.890 --> 00:50:33.098
There's no question about it.

00:50:33.098 --> 00:50:34.340
They can't do it themselves.

00:50:34.340 --> 00:50:36.590
They need the innate talent.

00:50:36.590 --> 00:50:41.890
They need mentorship and
resources and so forth.

00:50:41.890 --> 00:50:43.552
But they also just need luck.

00:50:43.552 --> 00:50:45.010
They need the right
time and place.

00:50:45.010 --> 00:50:47.200
They need to come
onto this earth,

00:50:47.200 --> 00:50:49.990
and find a place like
Davidson Academy,

00:50:49.990 --> 00:50:53.740
and find people like Ron and
Bill that could help them.

00:50:53.740 --> 00:50:55.140
And that's not so easy.

00:50:55.140 --> 00:50:59.180
We can't-- we can make our
own luck to a certain extent

00:50:59.180 --> 00:50:59.889
as a democracy.

00:50:59.889 --> 00:51:02.430
And we probably should make a
little bit more of our own luck

00:51:02.430 --> 00:51:03.200
in that regard.

00:51:03.200 --> 00:51:09.050
But most of the kids that have
that sort of innate capability

00:51:09.050 --> 00:51:11.430
